.TH SHOAL 1 "July 2026" "shoal 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
shoal \- structured, agent-native shell
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B shoal
[IOPTIONSR] [ISCRIPTR]
.br
.B shoal
fmt [--check] [IFILESR...]
.br
.B shoal
doctor [--json]
.br
.B shoal
lsp | mcp | completions ISHELLR
.SH DESCRIPTION
With no arguments on a terminal, starts the interactive shell. With a script
or standard input, evaluates deterministically without interactive init files.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR -c , " --command " ISOURCER
Evaluate source and exit.
.TP
.BR -h , " --help"
Print command help.
.TP
.BR -V , " --version"
Print the version.
.SH DEVELOPER COMMANDS
.TP
.B fmt
Canonical formatting; --check exits 1 when changes are required.
.TP
.B doctor
Installation and enforcement diagnostics; --json emits structured output.
.TP
.B lsp, mcp
Launch the corresponding companion process from PATH.
.TP
.B completions
Generate bash, zsh, or fish completion source.
